Module atu.software
Package ie.atu.sw.model

Record Class ExaminationPaper

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Record
ie.atu.sw.model.ExaminationPaper
Record Components:
paperId - Unique identifier for the examination paper.
moduleCode - Code of the module to which the examination paper belongs.
allowLogTables - Indicates whether log tables are allowed in the exam.
allowActuarialTables - Indicates whether actuarial tables are allowed.
allowStatisticalTables - Indicates whether statistical tables are allowed.
allowGraphPaper - Indicates whether graph paper is allowed.
allowDictionaries - Indicates whether dictionaries are allowed.
allowAttachedAnswerSheet - Indicates whether attached answer sheets are allowed.
allowThermodynamicTables - Indicates whether thermodynamic tables are allowed.
allowNonProgrammableCalculators - Indicates whether non-programmable calculators are allowed.
allowRateTables - Indicates whether rate tables are allowed.
totalQuestions - Total number of questions in the examination paper.
requiredAnswers - Number of answers required.
questions - List of questions included in the examination paper.
actions - List of actions taken by external examiners on this examination paper.
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public record ExaminationPaper(String paperId, String moduleCode, String allowLogTables, String allowActuarialTables, String allowStatisticalTables, String allowGraphPaper, String allowDictionaries, String allowAttachedAnswerSheet, String allowThermodynamicTables, String allowNonProgrammableCalculators, String allowRateTables, int totalQuestions, int requiredAnswers, List<Question> questions, List<ExternalExaminerAction> actions) extends Record implements Serializable
Represents an examination paper, detailing properties and actions taken by external examiners. This record holds all the attributes about an examination paper, such ID, module code, allowances for various materials during the exam, and the total number of questions. It also tracks a list of questions and actions performed by external examiners.
